                "content": "The fitness functions used in Genetic Algorithms for group formation may have, as unintended consequence, the creation of imbalanced groups. The authors propose a new Genetic Algorithm formation that looks for homogeneous social interactions despite heteregenous knowledge-levels. The authors compare the effectiveness of their approach against self-selection and random group formation.",
